-- INTERVIEW-Japan Taiyo Life to maintain foreign, domestic bond holdings
-- By Lisa Twaronite and Takefumi Ito
-- Mon Apr 21, 2014 01:27AM EDT
-- None



TOKYO, April 21 (Reuters) - Japan's Taiyo Life Insurance plans to maintain its holdings of foreign and domestic bonds in the current fiscal year through March 2015, a senior official said on Monday.

The insurer, a unit of T&D Holdings <8795.T>, sold 80 billion yen ($782.3 million) of domestic bonds in the fiscal year that ended in March and increased its foreign bond holdings by 280 billion yen, Junichi Yanai, general manager of the investment planning department, told Reuters in an interview.